Key Characteristics

  • Smallest capital analyzed (59k population). Best air quality!
  • Planned development advantages (newer state capital). Tribal majority population (57%+ Scheduled Tribe)
  • Itanagar demonstrates the health benefits of clean air and planned development - the lowest respiratory disease burden of all cities

    *Synthetic Data Considerations

  • Population: ~610,000-662,000 (metro 2025); literacy 89.52%; 70% Hindu, 14% Sanamahi, 10% Christian; sex ratio 1051/1000 (urban)
  • Respiratory Disease: High rates—Asthma 29.8%, COPD 15.6%, RTIs 11.3%; 28% asthma patients poorly controlled, 25.5% COPD patients severe
  • Healthcare: JNIMS (655 beds), Shija Hospital (350 beds), 26 private hospitals; state has 7 district hospitals, 17 CHCs, 95 PHCs; diagnostic centre shortage
  • Seasonal Patterns: Winter peaks—COPD 21.1% (winter) vs 8.1% (summer), RTIs 13.3% vs 4.1%; respiratory viruses surge Oct-Dec with high humidity
  • Socioeconomic: Rapid growth (19.2% annually); urban concentration of deprived population; highest consumption inequality in state; government/service economy
